**Adding a custom token (ETH,** 

**BSC, TRX)** 

**Before installing** 

To quickly add a token, you will need the following parameters: 

• **Token symbol\*** \- ticker symbol of the token (i.e. USDT). 

• **Token blockchain symbol\*** \- symbol of token's blockсhain. Supported only ETH (Ethereum), BNB (Binance Smart Chain), TRX (Tron). 

• **Token contract address\*** \- token's contract address in blockchain. Enter address with upper case symbols (i.e. 

0xdAC17F958D2ee523a2206206994597C13D831ec7). 

• **Token contract decimals\*** \- number of decimals in contract (i.e. 18). 

• **Precisions for pair \<ticker\>-USDT\*** \- numeric values from max to min, separated by comma for grouping orderbook (i.e. 10,1,0.1,0.01). 

• **Token custom price\*** \- set if there is no external price source (Binance, Kucoin). Set in USDT. 

• **Token name\***: \- (i.e. Bitcoin). 

• **Token logo URL:** \- permalink to square logo in png or svg (i.e.  

https://test.com/icon.svg). 

• **Decimals for rounding\*:** \- numeric value for rounding on trading and other pages. (i.e. 2 for 0.01 rounding). 

• **Token index\*:** \- token place in the list of coins at the wallet (i.e. 6). Default coins have 1...5 indexes. 

• **CoinMarketCap link:** \- link to coin's CoinMarketCap page 

• **Official site link:** \- link to coin's official page 

\* is for the required field. 

**Installation** 

• Connect via SSH to the server 

• Connect to the OpenCEX container: 

docker exec \-it opencex bash 

• Run the installation script: 

python manage.py add\_token 

• Enter all required parameters during the installation process 

• After successful installation, the script will display a message 

Token successfully added. Restart the backend to complete installation. 

• Exit the container with the command: 

exit 

• Restart the backend service : 

cd /app/opencex && docker compose restart 

**Adding a new blockchain to an existing token** 

To add a new network to an existing token, follow these steps: 

• Run quick token setup 

• Enter the same Token symbol in Token contract info 

• Enter another blockchain and fill in the rest of the items. 

• If the Token symbol matches, steps 2 and 3 are skipped and a new blockchain is added to the existing token. 

• Restart the backend 

**After the installation is complete** 

The script creates the base settings for the token when the installation completes: • Trading pair \<token\>-USDT. (Fees and Limits section on Pair Settings page in the admin panel.) 

• Token info. (Coins Management section on Info page in the admin panel.) 

• Limit and commission settings. (Fees and Limits section on Fee & Limit page in the admin panel). 

• Withdrawal settings. (Fees and Limits section on Withdrawal Fee page in the admin panel.) 

**Launching trading bots** 

To launch trading bots with a new pair, follow these steps: 

• Add balance necessary for trading to the bot user 

• Create a bot config for the new pair in the Bots section of the Settings page. Read more in ***How to set up a bot in a trading pair***. 

**Changing the icon of the added token** 

You can edit the token icon in the Coins Management section of the Info page in the admin panel. Specify a direct link to the token logo in **.svg** or **.png** format and click the Save button.   
![][image1]  
**Change grouping in the order book for a new pair** 

Grouping settings are located in the Fees and Limits section on the Pair Settings page in the admin panel. Specify numerical values separated by commas in the format:  **100,10,1,0.1,0.01** 

![][image2]The Precisions values are responsible for grouping settings in the order book on the trading page.
